-- Costco November same-store sales up 9 percent
-- 
-- Thu Dec 2, 2010 3:56am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/12/02/us-costco-idUSTRE6B11D120101202

 

 BANGALORE  (Reuters) - Costco Wholesale Corp ( COST.O ) posted a 9 percent rise in November sales at store open at least a year, helped by higher gasoline prices and strengthening foreign currencies. 

 The largest U.S. warehouse club company, which operates 582 warehouses across the world, recorded 13 percent same-store sales growth at its international segment in the month. Analysts were expecting same-store sales to rise 6.2 percent, according to Thomson Reuters data. For the four weeks ended November 28, net sales at Issaquah, Washington-based Costco rose 12 percent to $6.78 billion. (Reporting by  S. John Tilak  in Bangalore; Editing by Hans Peters)